title: Gunman kills 2 in New Zealand on the eve of the Women’s World Cup
description: A gunman killed two people before he died Thursday at a construction site in Auckland, New Zealand, as the nation prepared to host games in the FIFA Women’s World Cup soccer tournament, authorities said.

title: Cops haven’t verified most of Carlee Russell story, but she says nude photos were taken while missing
description: Police said Wednesday they've been unable to verify initial statements made by Carlee Russell, the Alabama woman who disappeared last week after after saying she saw a toddler walking on the interstate.

title: Poultry plant blames staffing company for hiring 16-year-old who was killed in workplace accident
description: Mar-Jac Poultry said Wednesday that it had no idea a 16-year-boy who was killed in an on-the-job accident was a minor.

title: 4 more Northwestern football alums underwent 'ritualized sexual' hazing, they say
description: Four more former Northwestern football players came forward on Wednesday to claim they were also subjected to "extreme ritualized sexual" hazing while at the prestigious Big Ten school.

title: Sen. Cynthia Lummis: Crypto regulation bill could prevent another FTX-style crisis
description: After a tumultuous year for crypto, a bipartisan duo in Congress is seeking to legitimize the industry by directing the U.S. government to formally regulate it.

title: Sheryl Crow says Jason Aldean is 'promoting violence' with a song that is 'not American'
description: Sheryl Crow has some harsh words for Jason Aldean and his new song, “Try That in a Small Town.”

title: Special counsel's target letter to Trump in 2020 election probe cites three federal statutes
description: Jack Smith's letter to Donald Trump in the 2020 election probe mentions statutes on deprivation of rights, conspiracy to defraud the U.S., and witness tampering.

title: How the 2024 Republicans boxed themselves in on Trump and Jan. 6
description: Donald Trump's rivals have largely shied away from criticizing his legal troubles — a strategy that has only strengthened the former president's bond with GOP voters.

title: A friend-finding app offered a ‘safe space’ for teens — sextortion soon followed
description: A Tinder-like app popular among teenagers and young adults has allegedly been used to extort users by tricking them into sending sexually explicit photos, a problem that internet safety watchdogs say is indicative of the challenges of keeping young people safe on social media.

title: Digital cleanup: How to tidy up cluttered devices
description: Got a full phone, cluttered desktop, or stuffed inbox? Then it’s time for a digital deep clean! Wirecutter’s Jason Chen joins TODAY to share his quick fixes to clean up devices and save storage space.

title: An Amazon-backed wind farm is coming to a struggling Mississippi Delta community
description: Amazon's involvement in a wind farm in Tunica County, Mississippi, has some residents hopeful but others questioning the tax incentives in an impoverished area.

title: Democrats question Hunter Biden whistleblower's claim of nonpartisanship
description: Gary Shapley says he is not affiliated with any political party, but he is represented by people with long-standing ties to the GOP.

title: Rare and dramatic fossil shows small mammal attacking larger dinosaur
description: While there is little doubt that many a Mesozoic mammal became a meal for a dinosaur, it may come as a surprise to learn that some mammals also dined on dinos.

title: Southern California school board rejects curriculum that mentions Harvey Milk
description: A Southern California school board has become the latest proxy for culture wars brewing across the country after a conservative bloc voted to formally reject state-endorsed curriculum that would have mentioned gay rights figure Harvey Milk.

title: Ron DeSantis allies press for a campaign shake-up
description: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. — The long knives are out for Florida Gov.

title: Alabama inmate James Barber, first to be executed after failed lethal injection attempts, says he's skeptical
description: James Barber, the first prisoner Alabama is preparing to put to death since a series of problematic lethal injection attempts prompted a pause in executions, says he is not fearful of dying this week but remains uneasy about the state’s ability to carry out the procedure.
